result.execSummary:
The defendant James Franklin Hagler Sr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Due to not following the payment plan agreement, specifically payment(s) were missed, the payment plan has been ended and the failure to pay action has been enforced.
Assessment for Attorney Fees in the amount of $294 entered as ordered by the court on 10/10/14 to pay $60.00 monthly.  Final payment due by 06/15/15. Failure to pay is a Civil Judgment.
Signed & Filed, Affdavit and Order for Payment of Attorney Fees and Costs.

Defendant James Franklin Hagler in court with attorney Laura M Habush.  Defendant James Franklin Hagler in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties and defendant. 
 Statements from Rodney L.
AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 12 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive, credit for 76 DAYS time served, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim Cecila N. unless approved by agent or court. 
-No contact with Zelma H., except during period of incarceration court allows no violent contact. Upon release agent is to revisit contact condition.
-Agent to set Probation Review Hearing Upon Release.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during probation period, failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
-Court WAIVED all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges.
-Provide DNA Sample.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
*Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. 
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

Filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
Received & Filed, WCS Report: In Custody Status.
Arguments from state and defesne as to No Contact Order. Court GRANED defense motion to REMOVE Rodney L. from order.

AS TO COUNT 2 & 3
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion from the state, the court ordered Counts 2 & 3 Dismissed, But Read In for Sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 1 AS AMENDED
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.Case adjourned to branch 23 for Sentencing.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant James Franklin Hagler in court with attorney Laura M Habush.  Defendant James Franklin Hagler in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Status Conference. Parties have reached a resolution.
AS TO COUNT 1 
On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to REMOVE the Repeater enhancer (939.62(1)(b).  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 3, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant James Franklin Hagler in court with attorney Laura M Habush (as a friend of the Court).  Defendant James Franklin Hagler in custody.  
 Katryna L Childs appeared for Matthew Puthukulam for the State of Wisconsin.
  Br. 4 for Br. 23:
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. 

Defendant has another case pending in Branch 20 (2013CF5815), scheduled for a Plea and Sentencing Hearing on 5-15-2014 at 1:30 pm.  Court to discuss on the next date, the Chief Judge's rule regarding the transfer of cases from the Domestic Violence Unit.     

For the reasons as stated on the record, Court appoints Laura Habush as counsel for defendant (on case 2014CF1635), at the rate of $60.00 per hour.  Attorney Habush agreed to the appointment by the Court.  Order signed and filed.  Defendant shall reimburse Milwaukee County at the rate of $60.00 per month commencing upon the conclusion of case.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court maintained the current cash bail in the amount of $250.00 on case 2014CF1635 and forfeited the cash bail in the amount of $500.00 on case 2014CM1281.  Monies to be held for recompense.  

Court ordered that the defendant may have contact with the victim while in custody ONLY.  No visitation allowed, once defendant is out of custody.    mld
